cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.PL

This paper deals with the problem of non-monotonic reasoning in intelligent systems, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also establishes a connection between logic and probability, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LO (logic in computer science) and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also mentions computational aspects of conditional probability logic, which could make it relevant to cs.CR (cryptography and security) and cs.PL (programming languages).
